solution.p:
We use the FOIL technique: First Outside Inside Last \begin{aligned}
              \left({x^{9}-13}\right)^2\amp =\left({x^{9}-13}\right)\left({x^{9}-13}\right)\\
                               \amp ={x^{18}-13x^{9}-13x^{9}+169}\\
                                \amp ={x^{18}-26x^{9}+169}
      \end{aligned}

Alternatively, we might observe that this is the square of the difference of two terms, in which case we may use the formula (a-b)^2=a^2-2ab+b^2 and write \begin{aligned}
              \left({x^{9}-13}\right)\left({x^{9}-13}\right)\amp =\left(x^{9}\right)^2-2\cdot x^{9}\cdot 13+13^2\\
                                \amp ={x^{18}-26x^{9}+169}
      \end{aligned} which is the same result we obtained using the FOIL method.
